Docs.summary: A collection of all the chart sheets in the specified or active workbook. Each chart sheet is represented by a object. This doesn’t include charts embedded on worksheets or dialog sheets. For information about embedded charts, see the object.

remarks.para: Use the property to return the Charts collection. Use the method to create a new chart sheet and add it to the workbook.
You can combine the method with the method to add a new chart that contains data from a worksheet.
Use Charts(), where is the chart sheet index number or name, to return a single Chart object.
The collection contains all the sheets in the workbook (both chart sheets and worksheets). Use Sheets(), where is the sheet name or number, to return a single sheet.
